This looks like applying the triangle inequality multiple times to the expression `RiemannSum F a b M - L`. 

Let's decompose `RiemannSum F a b M - L`:
```
RiemannSum F a b M - L = (RiemannSum F a b M - RiemannSum (f N) a b M) + (RiemannSum (f N) a b M - ℓ N) + (ℓ N - L)
```

Thus, taking absolute values and applying the triangle inequality:
```
|RiemannSum F a b M - L| ≤ 
  |RiemannSum F a b M - RiemannSum (f N) a b M| + 
  |RiemannSum (f N) a b M - ℓ N| + 
  |ℓ N - L|
